space-x-2 border-2 border-white text-white hover:bg-teal-600 px-8 py-4 rounded-xl font-semibold transition-colors","children":[["$","svg",null,{"ref":"$undefined","xmlns":"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg","width":24,"height":24,"viewBox":"0 0 24 24","fill":"none","stroke":"currentColor","strokeWidth":2,"strokeLinecap":"round","strokeLinejoin":"round","className":"lucide lucide-phone w-5 h-5","aria-hidden":"true","children":[["$","path","foiqr5",{"d":"M22 16.92v3a2 2 0 0 1-2.18 2 19.79 19.79 0 0 1-8.63-3.07 19.5 19.5 0 0 1-6-6 19.79 19.79 0 0 1-3.07-8.67A2 2 0 0 1 4.11 2h3a2 2 0 0 1 2 1.72 12.84 12.84 0 0 0 .7 2.81 2 2 0 0 1-.45 2.11L8.09 9.91a16 16 0 0 0 6 6l1.27-1.27a2 2 0 0 1 2.11-.45 12.84 12.84 0 0 0 2.81.7A2 2 0 0 1 22 16.92z"}],"$undefined"]}],["$","span",null,{"children":"844-967-5247"}]]}]]}]]}]}]}],["$","section",null,{"className":"py-20 bg-white","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"grid lg:grid-cols-3 gap-12","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"lg:col-span-2","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"font-heading text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-6","children":["What Does ","Commercial Auto"," Cover?"]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"space-y-4 mb-10","children":[["$","p","0",{"className":"text-slate-600 leading-relaxed","children":"A food truck is simultaneously a vehicle and a business location — and those two functions create two separate insurance needs. Commercial auto insurance covers your food truck while it's being driven: liability for accidents you cause on the road, physical damage to your truck from collisions and covered perils, and uninsured motorist protection. When your food truck is parked and you're serving customers, general liability takes over."}],["$","p","1",{"className":"text-slate-600 leading-relaxed","children":"Trailer coverage is essential for many concessionaires who tow their concession units to events. Trailers need to be specifically scheduled on your commercial auto policy to be covered. Both liability coverage (if your trailer causes an accident while being towed) and physical damage coverage (for the trailer itself) should be included. An unscheduled trailer creates significant gaps in your coverage."}],"$L1e","$L1f","$L20"]}],"$L21","$L22","$L23"]}],"$L24"]}]}]}],"$L25"]
1e:["$","p","2",{"className":"text-slate-600 leading-relaxed","children":"Hired and non-owned auto coverage extends your policy to cover vehicles you don't own but use for business. If you rent a truck to transport equipment, or if an employee uses their personal vehicle on your behalf, hired and non-owned auto provides the business liability protection your standard commercial auto policy may not extend to those vehicles."}]
1f:["$","p","3",{"className":"text-slate-600 leading-relaxed","children":"Equipment in transit coverage under commercial auto or inland marine protects your supplies and equipment while they're being transported. High-value equipment — generators, cooking equipment, display systems — represents significant investment. Coverage while in transit ensures that an accident on the way to an event doesn't leave you with a total loss."}]
20:["$","p","4",{"className":"text-slate-600 leading-relaxed","children":"Multi-state commercial auto coverage is important for vendors who travel to events in different states. Insurance requirements for commercial vehicles vary by state. Working with a specialist who understands interstate commerce and multi-state vendor operations ensures your coverage is compliant wherever your truck takes you."}]
21:["$","h2",null,{"className":"font-heading text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-6","children":["Who Needs ","Commercial Auto","?"]}]
22:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-10","children":"Any concessionaire who operates a food truck, drives a commercial vehicle to events, tows a concession trailer, or uses vehicles as part of their vendor operations. If you transport equipment, supplies, or a concession unit to events using any vehicle, commercial auto coverage is required by law and essential for your protection."}]
23:[["$","h2",null,{"className":"font-heading text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-6","children":"Frequently Asked Questions"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"space-y-4","children":[["$","div","0",{"className":"bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-6","children":[["$","h3",null,{"className":"font-heading font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-2","children":"Does my personal auto insurance cover my food truck?"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed","children":"No — personal auto policies exclude commercial use. If you're using a vehicle for your food vendor business, you need a commercial auto policy. Driving your food truck without commercial auto coverage creates significant uninsured exposure."}]]}],["$","div","1",{"className":"bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-6","children":[["$","h3",null,{"className":"font-heading font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-2","children":"Is my trailer covered under commercial auto?"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed","children":"Trailers can be covered under commercial auto, but they need to be specifically listed on the policy. Make sure your trailer is scheduled on your policy to ensure coverage for both liability and physical damage."}]]}],["$","div","2",{"className":"bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-6","children":[["$","h3",null,{"className":"font-heading font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-2","children":"What is hired and non-owned auto coverage?"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed","children":"Hired and non-owned auto coverage protects your business if you rent vehicles or your employees use their personal vehicles for business purposes. This is important for vendors who rent trucks or trailers for events."}]]}],["$","div","3",{"className":"bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-6","children":[["$","h3",null,{"className":"font-heading font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-2","children":"What if my food truck is used as a cooking location?"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed","children":"When your food truck is stationary and you're operating it as a food service location, general liability (not auto) covers customer injuries. Commercial auto covers vehicle-related incidents while driving."}]]}],["$","div","4",{"className":"bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-6","children":[["$","h3",null,{"className":"font-heading font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-2","children":"Do I need commercial auto if I only tow a trailer?"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed","children":"Yes — if you're using a personal vehicle to tow a business trailer, your personal policy may not cover business-related accidents. A commercial auto policy for the towing vehicle protects your business."}]]}]]}]]
